---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="shuttle new"
  description="Scaffold a new project with a framework-specific Dockerfile, shuttle.yml, and service configuration."
  section="commands"
>
  <p>
    <code>shuttle new</code> bootstraps a new project directory with everything you need to start
    developing and deploying: a framework-appropriate <code>Dockerfile</code>, a configured
    <code>shuttle.yml</code>, and service definitions. It guides you through setup with interactive
    prompts or uses defaults with <code>--yes</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle new [framework] [name] [flags]
</code></pre>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle new                           # interactive: prompts for framework and name
shuttle new laravel my-app            # skip framework and name prompts
shuttle new symfony my-api --yes      # use all defaults, no prompts
</code></pre>

  <h2>Arguments</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Argument</th>
        <th>Required</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>framework</code></td>
        <td>No</td>
        <td>Framework template to use: <code>laravel</code> or <code>symfony</code>. Prompted if not provided.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>name</code></td>
        <td>No</td>
        <td>Project directory name. Prompted if not provided. Also used as the app name in <code>shuttle.yml</code>.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Flags</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Flag</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--yes</code></td>
        <td><code>false</code></td>
        <td>Accept all defaults without interactive prompts</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Supported frameworks</h2>

  <h3>laravel</h3>
  <p>Interactive prompts (skipped with <code>--yes</code>):</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Database</strong>: PostgreSQL (default), MySQL, MariaDB, SQLite</li>
    <li><strong>Redis</strong>: yes/no (default: yes)</li>
    <li><strong>Laravel Horizon</strong> (queue dashboard): yes/no (default: yes)</li>
    <li><strong>Task scheduler</strong>: yes/no (default: yes)</li>
    <li><strong>Laravel Reverb</strong> (WebSocket server): yes/no (default: no)</li>
    <li><strong>Mailpit</strong> (dev email): yes/no (default: yes)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Generated files:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>shuttle.yml</code> with web service, worker service (if Horizon), scheduler service, and accessories</li>
    <li><code>Dockerfile</code> optimized for Laravel (PHP-FPM + Octane or Apache)</li>
    <li><code>.dockerignore</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>symfony</h3>
  <p>Interactive prompts (skipped with <code>--yes</code>):</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Database</strong>: PostgreSQL (default), MySQL, MariaDB, SQLite</li>
    <li><strong>Redis</strong>: yes/no (default: yes)</li>
    <li><strong>Symfony Messenger</strong> (async workers): yes/no (default: yes)</li>
    <li><strong>Worker replicas</strong>: integer (default: 2, shown only if Messenger is enabled)</li>
    <li><strong>Mailpit</strong> (dev email): yes/no (default: yes)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Generated files:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>shuttle.yml</code> with web service, worker services (if Messenger), and accessories</li>
    <li><code>Dockerfile</code> optimized for Symfony (FrankenPHP or Apache)</li>
    <li><code>.dockerignore</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Base prompts (all frameworks)</h2>
  <p>After selecting the framework, Shuttle prompts for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Domain</strong>: e.g., <code>my-app.example.com</code> (default: <code>&lt;name&gt;.example.com</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Server host</strong>: IP or hostname (default: <code>your-server-ip</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>SSH user</strong>: (default: <code>deploy</code>)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Next steps after scaffold</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">cd my-app
shuttle provision       # bootstrap the server
shuttle deploy          # first deploy
</code></pre>

  <h2>Safety check</h2>
  <p>
    Shuttle checks whether <code>shuttle.yml</code> already exists in the target directory before
    generating files. If it does, the command aborts with an error to prevent overwriting an
    existing project.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
